events.description: Marcus Aurelius and L. Commodus (who changes his name to Lucius Verus) become joint emperors of Rome on the death of Antoninus Pius.
events.html: • 161 – Marcus Aurelius and L. Commodus (who changes his name to Lucius Verus) become joint emperors of Rome on the death of Antoninus Pius.[1]

events.description: Konrad III von Hohenstaufen was elected king of Germany at Coblenz in the presence of the papal legate Theodwin.
events.html: • 1138 – Konrad III von Hohenstaufen was elected king of Germany at Coblenz in the presence of the papal legate Theodwin.[2]

events.description: The University of Paris issues the last in a series of condemnations of various philosophical and theological theses.
events.html: • 1277 – The University of Paris issues the last in a series of condemnations of various philosophical and theological theses.[3]

events.description: A peace treaty is signed between the Ottoman Empire and the Republic of Venice, ending the Ottoman–Venetian War and leaving Cyprus in Ottoman hands.
events.html: • 1573 – A peace treaty is signed between the Ottoman Empire and the Republic of Venice, ending the Ottoman–Venetian War and leaving Cyprus in Ottoman hands.[4]

events.description: Napoleon Bonaparte captures Jaffa in Palestine and his troops proceed to kill more than 2,000 Albanian captives.
events.html: • 1799 – Napoleon Bonaparte captures Jaffa in Palestine and his troops proceed to kill more than 2,000 Albanian captives.[5]

events.description: Emperor Napoleon I of France wins the Battle of Craonne.
events.html: • 1814 – Emperor Napoleon I of France wins the Battle of Craonne.[6]

events.description: Shrigley abduction: 15-year old Ellen Turner is abducted by Edward Gibbon Wakefield, a future figure in the establishment of colonies in South Australia and New Zealand.
events.html: • 1826 – Shrigley abduction: 15-year old Ellen Turner is abducted by Edward Gibbon Wakefield, a future figure in the establishment of colonies in South Australia and New Zealand.[7][8]

events.description: Senator Daniel Webster gives his "Seventh of March" speech endorsing the Compromise of 1850 in order to prevent a possible civil war.
events.html: • 1850 – Senator Daniel Webster gives his "Seventh of March" speech endorsing the Compromise of 1850 in order to prevent a possible civil war.[9]

events.description: Alexander Graham Bell is granted a patent for an invention he calls the "telephone".
events.html: • 1876 – Alexander Graham Bell is granted a patent for an invention he calls the "telephone".[10]

events.description: Second Boer War: Boers, led by Koos de la Rey, defeat the British at the Battle of Tweebosch.
events.html: • 1902 – Second Boer War: Boers, led by Koos de la Rey, defeat the British at the Battle of Tweebosch.[11]

events.description: The short-lived socialist Labin Republic is proclaimed.
events.html: • 1921 – The short-lived socialist Labin Republic is proclaimed.[12][13]

events.description: The Parliament House of Finland is officially inaugurated in Helsinki, Finland.
events.html: • 1931 – The Parliament House of Finland is officially inaugurated in Helsinki, Finland.[14]

events.description: Günther Prien and the crew of German submarine U-47, one of the most successful U-boats of World War II, disappear without a trace.
events.html: • 1941 – Günther Prien and the crew of German submarine U-47, one of the most successful U-boats of World War II, disappear without a trace.[15]

events.description: Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 307 crashes in Lynnhurst, Minneapolis, killing 15 people.
events.html: • 1951 – Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 307 crashes in Lynnhurst, Minneapolis, killing 15 people.[16]

events.description: Korean War: Operation Ripper: United Nations troops led by General Matthew Ridgway begin an assault against Chinese forces.
events.html: • 1951 – Korean War: Operation Ripper: United Nations troops led by General Matthew Ridgway begin an assault against Chinese forces.[17]

events.description: Iranian prime minister Ali Razmara is assassinated by Khalil Tahmasebi, a member of the Islamic fundamentalist Fada'iyan-e Islam, outside a mosque in Tehran.
events.html: • 1951 – Iranian prime minister Ali Razmara is assassinated by Khalil Tahmasebi, a member of the Islamic fundamentalist Fada'iyan-e Islam, outside a mosque in Tehran.[18][19]

events.description: Bloody Sunday: A group of 600 civil rights marchers are brutally attacked by state and local police in Selma, Alabama.
events.html: • 1965 – Bloody Sunday: A group of 600 civil rights marchers are brutally attacked by state and local police in Selma, Alabama.[20]

events.description: Aeroflot Flight 542 crashes in the Yermakovsky District, killing all 31 aboard.
events.html: • 1965 – Aeroflot Flight 542 crashes in the Yermakovsky District, killing all 31 aboard.[21]

events.description: The Majelis Permusyawaratan Rakyat Sementara (MPRS), Indonesia's provisional parliament, revoked Sukarno's mandate as President of Indonesia.
events.html: • 1967 – The Majelis Permusyawaratan Rakyat Sementara (MPRS), Indonesia's provisional parliament, revoked Sukarno's mandate as President of Indonesia.

events.description: Vietnam War: The United States and South Vietnamese military begin Operation Truong Cong Dinh to root out Viet Cong forces from the area surrounding Mỹ Tho.
events.html: • 1968 – Vietnam War: The United States and South Vietnamese military begin Operation Truong Cong Dinh to root out Viet Cong forces from the area surrounding Mỹ Tho.

entities.name: Army of the Republic of Vietnam

events.description: Sheikh Mujibur Rahman, political leader of then East Pakistan (present day-Bangladesh), delivers his historic 7th March speech in the Racecourse Field (Now Suhrawardy Udyan) in Dhaka.
events.html: • 1971 – Sheikh Mujibur Rahman, political leader of then East Pakistan (present day-Bangladesh), delivers his historic 7th March speech in the Racecourse Field (Now Suhrawardy Udyan) in Dhaka.

events.description: Challenger Disaster: Divers from the USS Preserver locate the crew cabin of Challenger on the ocean floor.
events.html: • 1986 – Challenger Disaster: Divers from the USS Preserver locate the crew cabin of Challenger on the ocean floor.

events.description: Lieyu massacre: Taiwanese military massacre of 19 unarmed Vietnamese refugees at Donggang, Lieyu, Kinmen.
events.html: • 1987 – Lieyu massacre: Taiwanese military massacre of 19 unarmed Vietnamese refugees at Donggang, Lieyu, Kinmen.

events.description: Iran and the United Kingdom break diplomatic relations after a fight over Salman Rushdie and his controversial novel, The Satanic Verses.
events.html: • 1989 – Iran and the United Kingdom break diplomatic relations after a fight over Salman Rushdie and his controversial novel, The Satanic Verses.

events.description: The tugboat Thomas Hebert sank off the coast of New Jersey, USA.
events.html: • 1993 – The tugboat Thomas Hebert sank off the coast of New Jersey, USA.

events.description: The terrorist organisation Lashkar-e-Taiba coordinates a series of bombings in Varanasi, India.
events.html: • 2006 – The terrorist organisation Lashkar-e-Taiba coordinates a series of bombings in Varanasi, India.

events.description: Reform of the House of Lords: The British House of Commons votes to make the upper chamber, the House of Lords, 100% elected.
events.html: • 2007 – Reform of the House of Lords: The British House of Commons votes to make the upper chamber, the House of Lords, 100% elected.

entities.name: Reform of the House of Lords

events.description: Garuda Indonesia Flight 200 crashes at Adisutjipto International Airport in the Special Region of Yogyakarta, Indonesia, killing 21 people.
events.html: • 2007 – Garuda Indonesia Flight 200 crashes at Adisutjipto International Airport in the Special Region of Yogyakarta, Indonesia, killing 21 people.[22]

events.description: The Real Irish Republican Army kills two British soldiers and injures two other soldiers and two civilians at Massereene Barracks, the first British military deaths in Northern Ireland since the end of The Troubles.
events.html: • 2009 – The Real Irish Republican Army kills two British soldiers and injures two other soldiers and two civilians at Massereene Barracks, the first British military deaths in Northern Ireland since the end of The Troubles.

events.description: At least 108 die and 615 are injured in the 2021 Bata explosions in Bata, Equatorial Guinea.
events.html: • 2021 – At least 108 die and 615 are injured in the 2021 Bata explosions in Bata, Equatorial Guinea.[23]

events.html: • 2024 – Sweden officially joins NATO, becoming its 32nd member.[24]
